   developed a body-oriented resilience training with elements of
   kickboxing: BEATVIC. The present study aims to evaluate the
   effectiveness of the intervention.
   Methods/Design: Seven mental health institutions in the Netherlands will
   participate in this study. Participants will be randomly assigned to
   either the BEATVIC training or the control condition: social activation.
   Follow-ups are at 6, 18 and 30 months. Short term effects on risk
   factors for victimization will be examined, since these are direct
   targets of the intervention and are thought to be mediators of
   victimization, the primary outcome of the intervention. The effect on
   victimization will be investigated at follow-up. In a subgroup of
   patients, fMRI scans will be made before and after the intervention
   period in order to assess potential neural changes associated with the
